all_findings.title: Unlimited Withdrawal: withdraw()
all_findings.description: Function `withdraw()` allows withdrawal without amount limits. Attacker can drain all available funds in single transaction. Missing: maxWithdrawal check or amount restrictions.

evidence.fix_suggestion: Add require(amount <= maxWithdrawal, 'Exceeds limit') or implement withdrawal limits per user/period

all_findings.title: Missing Access Control on Minting Function
all_findings.description: Function `mint()` is minting without access control modifiers. Any caller can invoke this function. NFTBTC C001/H001/H002: Add onlyOwner, onlyAdmin, or role-based access control.

evidence.fix_suggestion: Add modifier to function declaration: `function mint(...) external onlyOwner {...}`

all_fixes.explanation: Added onlyOwner modifier to critical function
all_fixes.diff:
--- original
+++ fixed
@@ -1 +1 @@
- function withdraw(
-         uint256 assets,
-         address receiver,
-         address owner
-     ) public virtual returns (uint256 shares) 
+ function withdraw(
+         uint256 assets,
+         address receiver,
+         address owner
+     ) public onlyOwner virtual returns (uint256 shares)
